<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1049510>
    dc:description "FIGURE 35. A, B Epidius typicus (SMF 4246). A epigynum, ventral view; B vulva, ventral view. C, D, E Epidius rubropictus. C right male palp, ventral view (MNHN 22347); D – E female from Sumatra (D epigynum, ventral view, E vulva, ventral view). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1049510/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1049506>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Epidius binotatus (MNHN 13670 / 1574). A ventral view of left male palp. B, C Epidius binotatus guineensis (MRAC 122567), right male palp (B ventral, C retrolateral). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1049506/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1049508>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. Epidius binotatus. A, B MRAC 202642; C, D, Syntype series MNHN 13670 / 1574. A, C epigynum, ventral view; B, D vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1049508/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

